### The Rust Core: What Exists Today

The `brinkmanship_engine/src` directory contains **5 production Rust files**:

| File | Purpose | Status |
|:---|:---|:---|
| `state.rs` | ECS-Lite entity/component schema | ✅ Production-ready |
| `chronos.rs` | Immutable tick engine (`im` crate) | ✅ Hardened + tested |
| `main.rs` | Axum REST API server | ✅ Live |
| `reactor.rs` | Event resolution pipeline | ✅ Functional |
| `ai_director_stress.rs` | 50-actor stress benchmark harness | ✅ Benchmarked (not production AI) |

**`state.rs` is the most important signal:** The `State` struct already implements a fully generic, ECS-Lite entity map — `metrics`, `demographics`, `ideology`, `industry`, and `diplomatic_ledgers` are all keyed by `EntityId`. The `IdeologyComponent` (Auth/Lib axis, Planned/Market axis, `overton_radius`) is **structurally implemented** in Rust. The foundation demanded by the Grand Strategy architecture audit is **already in place at the data layer.**

